This paper is about developing a conversational agent for the Amazon Alexa Prize challenge, which falls under the category of natural language processing and dialogue systems. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning and contextual ranking, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper addresses the problem of training on noisy and sparse feedback, which could fall under the sub-categories of social and information networks (cs.SD) or computers and society (cs.CY).
